{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, the elastic operator L EL satisfies the following fundamental property, proved in [21,28].Theorem 1 (From [21], Theorem 2.1 (i)).",
    "Under the assumptions (EL1)-(EL4), the linearized elastic operator L EL has an explicit spectral gap, i.e.",
    "there exists an explicit constant λ EL > 0 such that, for all f ∈ L 2 (R 3, µ µ µ -1/2), ( 27)L EL (f), f L 2 v µ -1 2 ≤ -λ EL f -π EL (f) 2 L 2 v ⟨v⟩ γ 2 µ -1 2,for any γ ∈ [0, 1].",
    "The constant λ EL depends only on the different masses (m i) 1≤i≤4 and on the collision kernels (B ij) 1≤i,j≤4.Properties of the linearized chemical operator L CH.",
    "We may prove in a very similar way that L CH is a closed, self-adjoint and nonpositive operator in the same space L 2 (R 3, µ µ µ -1/2)."
  ]
}